data.title: Dáil constituencies
data.meta_description: There are 39 multi-member electoral districts, known as Dáil constituencies, that elect 160 TDs, to Dáil Éireann, the house of representatives of the Oireachtas, Ireland's parliament, on the system of proportional representation by means of the single transferable vote (PR-STV), to a maximum term of five years. The configuration of constituencies and seats per constituencies has been reviewed, and is subject to Oireachtas approval.
